40|$|ABSTRACT. The {{subject of}} tax reform seems {{to emerge as}} a highly debated topic of {{discussion}} every few years because <b>our</b> current income <b>tax</b> system is too complex, inefficient, and intrusive. There are two unique proposals that would {{change the face of}} <b>our</b> <b>tax</b> system, the flat tax and the national sales tax. This paper examines these proposals on the grounds of complexity, efficiency, and intrusiveness to determine which plan would be the best substitute for <b>our</b> current income <b>tax</b> system...|$|R
